`/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/`

## What you need to do

### Step 1: Read these key existing files to understand the data shapes
- `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/app/api/chat/route.ts`
- `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/app/api/runtime-status/route.ts`
- `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/app/globals.css` (for existing styles like `omega-cosmic-bg`)
- `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/hooks/useVoiceEngine.ts` (first 100 lines — understand the interface)
- `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/app/page.tsx` (existing page to understand what to replace)

### Step 2: Write all required files

Write these files (full, production-ready TypeScript/TSX):

**1. `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/app/page.tsx`**
Replace with the user's component above. Make it a proper Next.js client component (add `'use client'` at top). Fix the import paths to work with Next.js app router.

**2. `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/hooks/use-mobile.ts`**
Simple hook: returns true if window width < 768px. Use `useState` + `useEffect` + resize listener.

**3. `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/hooks/use-omega-chat.ts`**
Full chat hook. Must provide:
- `conversations: Conversation[]` — list of all conversations
- `activeConvoId: string` — currently active conversation ID
- `activeConvo: Conversation | undefined` — current conversation object with messages
- `isStreaming: boolean` — whether AI is currently responding
- `systemState: SystemState` — runtime state object
- `telemetry: TelemetryEntry[]` — telemetry entries for the right panel
- `sendMessage(text: string): void` — sends a message, streams response from `/api/chat`
- `retryMessage(messageId: string): void` — retries last failed message
- `newConversation(): void` — creates new conversation
- `switchConversation(id: string): void` — switches active conversation
- `deleteConversation(id: string): void` — deletes a conversation

Message type: `{ id: string, role: 'user'|'assistant', content: string, timestamp: number, status?: 'streaming'|'done'|'error' }`
Conversation type: `{ id: string, title: string, messages: Message[], createdAt: number }`
SystemState type: `{ provider: string, model: string, status: 'online'|'degraded'|'offline', memoryEntries: number, mode: 'public'|'operator', uptime?: string }`
TelemetryEntry type: `{ id: string, timestamp: number, type: string, label: string, value: string | number }`

The sendMessage function must:
- Call POST `/api/chat` with `{ messages: [...history, { role: 'user', content: text }] }`
- Stream the response using `ReadableStream` / `getReader()`
- Update the streaming message in real-time
- On completion, add a telemetry entry

Also poll `/api/runtime-status` every 30s to update systemState.

**4. `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/hooks/use-voice.ts`**
Thin wrapper around the existing `useVoiceEngine` at `@/hooks/useVoiceEngine`. Must expose:
- `voiceState: { mode: 'idle'|'listening'|'speaking'|'voice-mode', transcript?: string }`
- `isSupported: boolean`
- `startListening(): void`
- `stopListening(): void`
- `enterVoiceMode(): void`
- `exitVoiceMode(): void`
- `interruptSpeech(): void`
- `updateSettings(settings: any): void`

Read the existing `useVoiceEngine.ts` to understand its interface and wrap it properly.

**5-13. All components in `/home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web/src/components/omega/`**

Write each component as a full, polished TSX file. Use Tailwind CSS classes. The visual style should be dark cosmic/space aesthetic (blacks, deep purples, cyan accents, glowing effects) matching the `omega-cosmic-bg` class. All components must be `'use client'` if they use hooks/state.

**`OmegaHeader.tsx`**
Props: `{ systemState: SystemState, onOpenSettings, onOpenSystemState, onToggleLeftPanel, onToggleRightPanel, showPanelToggles: boolean }`
Shows: OmegA logo/wordmark on left, system status badge (provider name, online/degraded indicator), panel toggle buttons, settings gear icon.

**`ChatView.tsx`**
Props: `{ messages: Message[], onRetry: (id:string)=>void, voiceSupported: boolean, onEnterVoice: ()=>void }`
Shows: Scrollable message list. User messages right-aligned dark bubble. Assistant messages left-aligned with subtle glow. Streaming messages show animated cursor. Empty state shows OmegA logo/welcome. Scroll to bottom on new messages. Voice button floating bottom-right if voiceSupported.

**`ChatComposer.tsx`**
Props: `{ onSend: (text:string)=>void, onPlusClick: ()=>void, onMicClick: ()=>void, disabled: boolean, isListening: boolean }`
Shows: Full-width text input with send button, plus (+) button on left, mic button that glows red when isListening. Submit on Enter (shift+enter for newline). Textarea auto-expands.

**`ConversationSidebar.tsx`**
Props: `{ conversations, activeId, onSelect, onNew, onDelete, isOpen, onClose }`
On desktop: fixed-width left panel (w-64), always visible when isOpen=true, slides in/out.
On mobile: full-height drawer overlay.
Shows: "New Chat" button at top, list of conversations with title + timestamp. Active conversation highlighted. Delete button on hover. "OmegA" branding at bottom.

**`TelemetryPanel.tsx`**
Props: `{ entries: TelemetryEntry[], isOpen, onClose }`
Right sidebar (w-72). Shows telemetry stream — each entry shows type badge, label, value, timestamp. Latest entries at top. Scrollable. Dark styling with subtle borders.

**`VoiceMode.tsx`**
Props: `{ voiceState, onStartListening, onStopListening, onExit, onInterrupt }`
Full-screen overlay that appears when voiceState.mode === 'voice-mode'. Shows animated orb, transcript text, interrupt/exit buttons. Cosmic visual design.

**`SystemStateDrawer.tsx`**
Props: `{ state: SystemState, isOpen, onClose }`
Slide-in drawer (bottom on mobile, right panel on desktop). Shows: provider, model, status, memory count, mode, uptime. Formatted in a telemetry/terminal style.

**`SettingsModal.tsx`**
Props: `{ isOpen, onClose, voiceSettings, onUpdateVoice }`
Modal dialog. Has tabs: Voice (TTS voice selection, speed), Display. Clean modal with dark overlay.

**`ActionSheet.tsx`**
Props: `{ isOpen, onClose, onNewConversation, onAttachNote }`
Bottom sheet (mobile) or small dropdown (desktop). Options: New Conversation, Attach Note. Smooth slide-up animation.

### Step 3: Add `omega-cosmic-bg` CSS class if not already in globals.css

Check globals.css. If `omega-cosmic-bg` isn't defined, add it:
```css
.omega-cosmic-bg {
  background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 20% 50%, #0d0221 0%, #000000 40%, #0a0a1a 100%);
}
```

### Step 4: Ensure `'use client'` is on page.tsx since it uses hooks

### Step 5: Deploy to Vercel

After writing all files, run:
```bash
cd /home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web && npx vercel --prod --yes 2>&1 | tail -20
```

If vercel CLI isn't logged in, instead just do a git push and let Vercel auto-deploy:
```bash
cd /home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture && git add -A && git status
```
Then report what needs to happen for deploy.

## Important notes
- Read the existing `/api/chat/route.ts` FIRST to know the exact request/response format
- Read `useVoiceEngine.ts` FIRST so `use-voice.ts` wraps it correctly  
- All components use Tailwind CSS (it's already configured in the project)
- The project is Next.js 16 with React 19 — use app router patterns
- Do NOT install new packages — only use what's in the existing package.json
- TypeScript strict mode — type everything properly
- After writing files, verify the build works: `cd /home/mega/OMEGA_WORKSPACE/CANON/OmegA-Architecture/web && npm run build 2>&1 | tail -40`

